race.comment: KAZARU (12) looks very well placed here. She improved nicely second up at Pakenham when rising to 1600m, getting home powerfully for second, beaten a long neck. She showed good ability last time in and looks very much suited going to 1717m now. SOMETHINGSOSTRONG (10) looks ready to peak third up, another that improved nicely second up when getting home well at Geelong. She was well backed there and can atone here. SAINT LOUIS BLUE (7) has been good in two runs to date, working home well behind KAZARU at Pakenham for third. Tough draw here but he can continue to progress. OR AM I (13) wasn't far away at Werribee last time and is in the mix.
